import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data.groupby('state').count()['city']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(state_counts.index, state_counts.values)
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count of Cities')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of cities across different states?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    ax.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_title('What is the geographical distribution of cities in the dataset?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_count = data['city'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(city_count.index, city_count.values)
    plt.title('What is the most common city in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(city_count.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Most common city: {city_count.index[0]} ({city_count.max():.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['lon'])
    plt.hist(data['lon'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['lon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lon'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities across different longitude values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['lat'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['lat'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
